<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Solving for 'left' on absolutely positioned non-replaced elements</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="When direction is 'rtl' and 'width' and 'left' are 'auto' and 'right' is not 'auto', the 'width' becomes shrink-to-fit and then solve for 'left'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #div1
            {
                border: solid;
                direction: rtl;
                height: 3in;
                position: relative;
                width: 3in;
            }
            div div
            {
                background-color: orange;
                left: auto;
                position: absolute;
                right: 0;
                width: auto;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the "Filler Text" below is contained within an orange box of the same width as the text and the orange box is in the top-right corner of the black box.</p>
        <div id="div1">
            <div>Filler Text</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>